    "traps": "Watch the listing-style question (training + rewards + leading by example + open door): the right answer is <strong>ensuring adherence to an ethics code</strong>, not 'improving productivity' or 'increasing profits.' Don't confuse <strong>recruiting</strong> (finding applicants) with <strong>orienting</strong> (welcoming a hire already made). HR covers all four functions — plan, staff, lead, organize — not just hiring."
