  "SM": {
    "name": "Strategic Management",
    "summary": "<strong>Expect about 1 question</strong> from Strategic Management on the Finance ICDC exam. DECA tests the <strong>concept of management</strong> and its functions, <strong>factors that affect management</strong> (like span of control), and <strong>risk management</strong> — including the financial risks a firm faces. Frame it around how a finance company is organized and how it protects itself from loss.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "h": "Concept and functions of management (SM:001)",
        "items": [
          "<strong>Management</strong> coordinates resources to reach goals. DECA tests the four functions: <strong>planning, organizing, leading (directing), and controlling</strong>. The 2018 answer for identifying jobs and assigning them to departments was <strong>organizing</strong>.",
          "A manager who motivates staff toward company goals is <strong>leading</strong> (2017). Recognize the function by what the manager is <em>doing</em>.",
          "Management uses <strong>resources</strong>: the 2023 exam tested <strong>material resources</strong> (physical things like equipment or supplies) versus human or financial resources."
        ]
      },
      {
        "h": "Factors that affect management (SM:100)",
        "items": [
          "<strong>Span of control</strong> is how many employees report to one manager. The 2022 answer: a manager with only two direct reports has a <strong>narrow span of control</strong>; many direct reports is a <strong>wide span</strong>.",
          "Narrow spans allow closer supervision but create more management layers — relevant in a bank where compliance demands tight oversight."
        ]
      },
      {
        "h": "Risk management (SM:075, SM:076)",
        "items": [
          "<strong>Risk management</strong> identifies and limits potential losses. DECA tests types: an <strong>external financial risk</strong> (2020) comes from outside the firm's control, like interest-rate or market changes.",
          "Spending all financial resources to chase one breakthrough is a <strong>speculative risk</strong> (2024) — it could produce a gain or a loss, unlike a pure risk (loss only).",
          "Event/operational planners <strong>control and limit risk</strong> (2021) to protect people, assets, and the firm's finances — e.g., insurance and contingency plans."
        ]
      }
    ],
    "traps": "Identify the <strong>management function</strong> by the verb: organizing = assigning jobs/departments; leading = motivating people; controlling = measuring results; planning = setting goals. Don't mix them up. On risk: <strong>speculative risk</strong> can gain or lose (an investment), while <strong>pure risk</strong> can only lose (a fire) — and know <strong>internal vs. external</strong> financial risk by whether the firm controls the cause. A <strong>narrow</strong> span = few reports, a <strong>wide</strong> span = many."
  }
